  "local_port": 41238,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "If you're receiving likes from people in India despite targeting your ad campaign exclusively to San Francisco (SF), there could be several reasons for this occurrence. Let's consider some possible explanations:\n\n1. **Ad Visibility Beyond Targeting**: \n   - Sometimes, ads can be shared or discussed on social media platforms outside of the targeted region. If someone from India sees your ad shared by a friend in SF, they could like it or engage with it directly.\n\n2. **Organic Reach**:\n   - If your ad has a public page or profile associated with it, people from anywhere in the world, including India, can see and interact with your content organically, beyond the paid ad targeting.\n\n3. **Incorrect Audience Data**:\n   - There might be inaccuracies in the user data that social media platforms use for targeting. Some users from India might have their location set to SF, either intentionally or due to an error.\n\n4. **Platform Algorithm**:\n   - Social media algorithms can sometimes show ads to a broader audience than intended, especially if the ad performs well. This can result in likes from unintended geographic regions.\n\n5. **Ad Leakage**:\n   - This is a phenomenon where ads \"leak\" outside of their targeted audience due to various platform-side issues or optimizations that prioritize engagement over strict targeting.\n\n6. **Cross-Platform Engagement**:\n   - If your campaign spans multiple platforms or if users share content across different social media, it can result in engagement from unintended audiences.\n\n**Steps to Address This Issue:**\n\n1. **Review Campaign Settings**:\n   - Double-check your ad campaign settings to ensure the geographic targeting is set correctly to SF only.\n\n2. **Analyze Engagement Data**:\n   - Use analytics tools provided by the advertising platform to see where the engagement is coming from. This can help identify if there's a pattern or a specific cause.\n\n3. **Contact Support**:\n   - If the issue persists, reach out to the support team of the advertising platform. They can provide insights into why your ads are reaching unintended audiences.\n\n4. **Adjust Strategy**:\n   - Consider adjusting your campaign strategy to minimize organic reach outside your target if it's affecting your metrics or budget allocation.\n\n5. **Monitor and Iterate**:\n   - Continuously monitor your campaign's performance and make adjustments as needed to ensure it aligns with your targeting goals.\n\nBy understanding these factors and taking appropriate action, you can better align your ad campaign's performance with your intended geographic targeting.",
